[SN]TITLE[SN]
Glenn Loovens: Sheffield Wednesday centre-back injures ankle

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Sheffield Wednesday centre-back Glenn Loovens will miss the start of the season after suffering an ankle injury.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Dutchman requires surgery, which is expected to keep him out for up to eight weeks.
The 32-year-old made 38 appearances for the Owls last season to help them reach the Championship play-off final, where they suffered a 1-0 defeat by Hull.
He has played a total of 93 games for the club since joining in December 2013 following his release by Real Zaragoza.
